      It's time to raid the ABC wardrobe department again, for the       
       Spicks and Specks: Australiana Special. Joining Adam 'Molly       
       Meldrum' Hills is 'Split Enz'-inspired Alan Brough and Myf        
    'Chrissy Amphlett' Warhurst. Alan's team is made up of Gabriella     
   'Olivia Newton-John' Cilmi and 'AC/DC'-inspired Dave O'Neil, while    
     Myf is joined by 'Purple Wiggle' Troy Cassar-Daly and Nick Cave     
        look-a-like Frank Woodley. Our teams tackle all manner of        
      Australiana-related questions and games. In Look What They've      
     Done, teams must work out which songs are being played by Wayne     
     Thorpe on the gumleaf. In a special new game The Boys and Girls     
    Line Up, teams have to match up three Aussie artists to the three    
      quirky facts about them. Joining the line-up is opera singer       
     Antoinette Halloran, Leonardo's Bride Abby Dobson, rock singer      
    Wendy Stapleton, conductor Benjamin Northey, Uncanny X-Man Brian     
    Mannix, and Kram from Spiderbait. To close the show Doug Goodman     
   and Wacca the Gumtree Drummer perform a unique version of Waltzing    
                                Matilda.
